milestones.description: Alei Nao and Chad Soper's 28-run partnership is PNG's highest for the 10th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 27 between Alei Nao and Norman Vanua
Mahuru Dai has become the top wicket-taker for PNG in ODIs with 15 wickets, going past Chad Soper's 13
Berrington has broken the record for most catches (23) in ODIs for SCOT, going past Mommsen's 22
This is the lowest match aggregate (295) involving teams P.N.G. & Scotland in ODIs
Mahuru Dai has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (11) for PNG, going past Vani Morea

stories.title: MacLeod, seamers lead Scotland to six-wicket win
stories.subTitle: Papua New Guinea v Scotland, 1st ODI, Dubai, November 24, 2017
stories.seoTitle: Calum MacLeod, seamers lead Scotland to six-wicket win
stories.summary: Safyaan Sharif and Alasdair Evans shared seven wickets between them to bowl Papua New Guinea out for 147, and Calum MacLeod's unbeaten 60 helped Scotland easily finish the chase
